# Next.js + shadcn (Marham)

## Stack

- **Next.js App Router** — read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using APIs; this version may differ from training data.
- **UI**: shadcn/ui only (`components/ui/`). Add new primitives via `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`.
- **Icons**: `lucide-react` only.
- **Never** add other UI libraries (MUI, Chakra, Ant Design, Bootstrap, Headless UI direct imports, styled-components, etc.).

## Styling

- **Tailwind only** — no inline `style={{}}`, no CSS modules, no new global CSS unless extending `app/globals.css`.
- Use colors already defined in `app/globals.css`:
  - Semantic: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, `bg-muted`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `ring-ring`, etc.
  - Brand: `bg-maingreen`, `text-darknavy`, `bg-brandblue`, `bg-skyblue`, `bg-pagegray`, `text-maingray`, `bg-mainblue`, `text-mainred`, etc.
- Prefer Tailwind token classes (`bg-skyblue`) over raw hex or `var(--color-*)` in className.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to merge classes.

## Folder structure

```
app/              → routes only (thin pages)
components/ui/    → shadcn primitives (do not edit heavily)
components/<feature>/  → feature UI (doctors, layout, logo, …)
hooks/            → use-* hooks
lib/              → data, utils, config, API clients (consume MarhamOne — never host APIs)
```

See `api-consumption.mdc` for the no-Next.js-API rule.

## Page routes (`app/**/page.tsx`)

Keep pages **minimal** — fetch data, pass props, compose components:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — page is a thin orchestrator
export default async function Page({ params }: PageProps) {
  const data = getData(await params)
  return (
    <main className="bg-white min-h-screen">
      <FeatureHero {...data} />
      <FeatureList items={data.items} />
    </main>
  )
}
```

- No large JSX blocks, forms, or business logic in page files.
- Move UI to `components/<feature>/`, data/logic to `lib/`.
- Use `"use client"` only in components that need interactivity — keep pages as Server Components when possible.

## Components

- PascalCase files: `DoctorCard.tsx`, `site-header.tsx` (match existing folder convention).
- Feature components live under `components/<feature>/`, not in `app/`.
- Reuse shadcn primitives (`Button`, `Sheet`, `DropdownMenu`, …) from `@/components/ui`.
- Imports use `@/` alias.

## Code style

- Functional components, TypeScript interfaces for props.
- Small focused components — split when a file grows past ~150 lines.
- Minimal diffs; match existing patterns in the codebase.
